article.headline: Vermont 79, Maine 48
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Mike Trimboli scored 15 points and Chris Holm had 13 Wednesday as Vermont overwhelmed Maine, 79-48. The game was tied at 16-16 with 11 minutes to play in the first half before Vermont (11-12, 7-6) took control with an 11-0 run over five minutes where it did not allow a Maine field goal. Trimboli and Holm were among six Catamounts to score six points in the first half as UVM jumped out to a 40-24 lead at the break. Vermont never looked back as Trimboli went 5-for-8 from the floor and four of five three-point attempts along with six assists. Holm led the Vermont inside effort making six of his 10 field goal attempts and had eight rebounds. Josh Duell chipped in with seven points, five rebounds and a career-high seven assists. Ryan Schneider had 11 points and eight boards. Chris Bruff led Maine (9-15, 4-9) with 11 points and six rebounds while Phillipe Tchekane Bofia tallied 10 points.
